Question: What was the best thing about your Summer? What are you looking forward this Fall?
Answer:
I feel like it's still going. AZ seems summer-like all the time. Even winter is 70-80s at times. Only really gets cold in the morning and night.
  
  Salt water rafting was fun besides the sunburn and some rafts popping since we kept hitting trees! Too many people with us and had no way to move. The music choices was annoying  (all Spanish ) got hit with marshmallows which was gross yet fun.
  
  ended up going offroading at Lake Pleasant and checking out the campgrounds there. Lots of donkey friends chilling. Think one might have been pregnant. swam at two different spots there.
  
  I really need to get a passport since I could have gone to Mexico with everyone on July 4th.. looked fun. They still talk about it. hotel right on the ocean, a few pools and hot tub etc
  
  some family parties.. one of their friends was going back to Ecuador so they hosted a party for her.
  
  gone to my brother's country club hes a member at
  
  we're supposed to go camping in Sedona but i don't know when yet.
  
  fall... I guess Halloween. The town has a challenge of best decorated, haunted houses and best business for the community. People go really crazy with it! My sister and her husband got 3rd last year in one of the winning categories. I'm not sure what the theme will be this year but last year they did an alien thing. You get to vote on all the ones, shows maps of houses competing in it so you know what to check out. its just fun!

Question: What happens in the bubblegum game?
Answer:
"Have the children gather in a tight circle and make a fist with both hands. Then, have them hold their fists out in the centre of the circle. Select someone to be the "counter".
  
  The counter takes one of their fists and tap everyone's fists (including their own) as they say this rhyme: "Bubble gum, Bubble gum, in a dish. How many pieces do you wish?"
  
  Whoever they tap last says a number between 1 and 20. Then the counter taps everyone's fists again as they count to the specified number.
  
  Whoever they land on last, has to take that fist out of the circle and place it behind their back. Then the counter would start all over again with "Bubble gum, Bubble gum ..." and repeat the process.
  
  Once both fists are tapped, that person is out. And this goes on until it narrowed it down to one - the winner!"

yes.

  - the first time we officially moved in my mom and I were watching tv. We moved from a 3 family house so naturally was used to other people making noise. It dawned on us at the same time that this was a legit house and nobody else was home/above us. We heard someone moving furniture  (at this time the whole upstairs was still being worked on - there was no furniture up there). We also heard someone going up and down the staircase.
  
  - A ghost in one of my prom pictures.
  
  - bullet casings rolling towards you on the floor where none were before
  
  - the kitchen ceiling was being taken down. His mom had a table with those Spanish mosaics on it and one of the tiles ended up falling down from the ceiling and landed right into my dad's shirt pocket.
  
  - my sister and her then ex were alone at the house and the smoke alarm kept beeping. They even took out the batteries and it was still going off.
  
  - I saw this weird shadow thing. It was just sitting at the table staring my way. I ended up trying to get a closer look at it. I then felt like I couldn't move, couldn't talk or scream. I felt frozen in place. Then a calmness settled over me. The shadow was gone. I went back to sleep. I know that I was awake since I don't dream of monster like stuff. It was really bizarre!
  
  -
  
  One time in Maine, my mom and I were driving to the store at night. These "people" ended up coming out of thin air. We served.
